oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Effect of Modified Live Bovine Viral Diarrhea Virus (BVDV) Vaccination During the Third Trimester of Pregnancy in Beef Cows
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Fleming, Sherrill A.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: persistent infection
BVDV
vaccinate
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Sixteen Brahman-Angus Fl cows (3 years old) were found to be negative for persistent BVDV infection by virus isolation on Buffy coat samples between approximately 180-270 days of gestation. Two weeks later cows were randomly assigned to vaccinate and nonvaccinate groups.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1996; 155-156
